Positive Feedback Transmissions

   This Game is Awesome! Teamwork makes the dream work.
   Greg, Colin, Nick & Tim Kinda Funny

   It's challenging, but in a way that can be understood by anyone from a
   hardened puzzle fan to kids and grandparents.
   Colin Campbell Polygon

   If you have a girlfriend or a boyfriend who wasn’t into gaming, this is
   the game to play with them.
   CJ Andriessen Destructoid

   If we're gonna declare anything as game of PAX this is the one.
   SAM MACHKOVECH ArsTechnica

   death squared is all about observation and teamwork - it facilitates a
   social experience in front of a tv, people of all ages are able to play
   together
   Miles Martignoni The Guardian

   A game full of laughs and creative destruction that can also bring
   people together
   Tosin Onafowokan Geeks of Doom

   A game where everyone can feel like part of the solution.
   TJ Denzer Arcade Sushi

   4 players, all shouting commands over the top of each other and
   bursting out with laughter when we were accidentally decimated or a
   friend fell off the edge.
   Brodie Fogg Finder.com.au

   ..It’s not too complicated, not too frustrating, and rewarding enough
   that both players will find it hard to put down the controller
   Caleb Taylor Slickster Magazine

   There’s a surprising amount of depth to these puzzles
   Tim Poon Platform Nation

   One of the most fun things I played on the show floor
   Tom Marks PC Gamer Show

   Put your hand-eye coordination and relationship to the test with Death
   Squared.
   Stephen del Prado Player2

   This game is an absolute blast to play. 10/10 would die again.
   DecoyEC The Sebie

   It reminded me a lot of a charming game ilomilo
   Tally Callahan Co-Optimus

   No matter what, you are going to kill each other many, many times.
   Jacob Wood Indie Hangover

   I get asked a lot to recommend co-op games that don't involve shooting.
   You want Death Squared.
   Susan Arendt GamesRadar+ and Queen Nerd

   Loved playing Death Squared at #PAXEast.It may result in divorces and
   broken friendships,but so fun!
   Neha Tiwari Gamespot

   if you loved Portal, you'll love Death Squared
   2old2play 2 Old 2 Play

   a game entrenched with all the satisfaction and frustration you’d
   expect to either galvanise a team, or tear apart fragile alliances
   Hayden Waugh Power Up Gaming

